r? @nikomatsakis

(rust_highfive has picked a reviewer for you, use r? to override)

Am I right, this PR should fix link errors on msvc platforms that look like https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/28169?
The problem is that it still crashes on the freshest nightly :(

Hm yeah this should fix issues like that, what version of the compiler are you using? I just downloaded the latest nightly and tested it out and it worked for me, so perhaps a stale download link was used? Or maybe the wrong compiler?
ah, also nominating for a backport to beta

I tried the `x86_64` and it really worked! But what I am really interested in is `i686`...
